sub_title: Major Sport Events, Freelance sport event and project manager
summary:
Ten plus years experience working for different organisations to deliver international events. My passion for event management combined with my leadership skills helps to bring out the best in people so as to achieve their goals.
2020 Tokyo Paralympics Games as Technical Official. Best Technical Official nominee in Europe 2020/21

Experience includes:
- Planning and organising events in Europe and Middle East
- Co-ordinated local and remote teams globally building relationships with people from diverse cultural and professional backgrounds
- Ability to delegate tasks, motivate teams and work to tight deadlines
- Resourceful and creative, foreseeing possible problems and coming up with creative solutions
- Health and Safety aware
- Background in account management and sales where strong relationship management and negotiation skills were developed
- Business development skills developed working in international companies and supporting start-ups 
- Creates and delivers presentations to diverse audiences for training purposes 
- Collaborates with professional stakeholders and organisations
- Delivers high-level international sport competitions
- Marketing and brand awareness including for sports 
- Ensures contract compliance
- Bi-lingual and travelled extensively including having lived in Hungary, Lithuania, Czech Republic, France, Belgium and The Netherlands
- Level 3 Technical Official for World Triathlon
- Commitment to quality
- Planning, managing and delivering events are challenging and very rewarding process for me which leads to a whole range of positive outcomes for participants and partners
